Defendant Alonzo Romelle Kimble-Hinton in court with attorney Valeria Lenise Taylor.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case set for sentencing hearing. State placed nogiations on the record. Court found the state complied with victim rights legislation. Statements made as to sentencing.  
As to Count 1 as Amended:  
Court ordered defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, credit for 4 days time served.

Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on probation for 1 YEAR with the following conditions:

1) Court set restitution at zero;
2) Complete 40 hours of community service; 
3) Maintain employment of at least 20 hours per week. If not employed at least 20 hours per week be enrolled in at least 9 credit hours of educational programming; 
4) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharges;
5) No contact with any Hollister store locations; 
6) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

Court will not accept good faith efforts to complete any conditions of probation.

Court will authorize expungment upon successful completion of all conditions of probation.

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
